						<summary>

						<p>Chōḻa, Rājakēsarivarman, 4th year = c. 10th Century.</p>						

						<p>A temple girl of Tiruvaraṅgam by name Chēndaṉ Cheyyavāymaṇi made a gift of 10 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> of gold for burning a lamp and for bringing a pot of water from the river daily to the temple of Teṉkayilāyattu-Mahādēva at Śrīkaṇṭha-chaturvēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						<p>(Published in <hi rend="italic">SII</hi>, Vol. XIII, No. 88).</p>						

